A massive saltwater crocodile resting motionless in murky swamp water at golden hour, only its ancient eyes and ridged back visible above the surface, reflecting the amber light of a setting sun. The scene is rendered in Studio Ghibli style with soft, painterly textures and rich earthy greens and warm oranges. Delicate lily pads float nearby, and twisted mangrove roots frame the composition. The crocodile's expression conveys timeless patience and quiet intelligence, its scales detailed with careful brushwork. Fireflies begin to emerge in the humid air, adding subtle points of magical light to the contemplative, slightly mysterious atmosphere.
